1
00:00:00,718 --> 00:00:06,144
Airey mouse, airey mouse fly over my head

2
00:00:06,144 --> 00:00:10,771
And you shall have a crust of bread

3
00:00:10,771 --> 00:00:14,919
And when I brew, or when I bake,

4
00:00:14,919 --> 00:00:19,516
You shall have a piece of my wedding cake.

5
00:00:19,867 --> 00:00:20,745
Early bitten,

6
00:00:20,745 --> 00:00:22,021
breakfast smitten,

7
00:00:22,021 --> 00:00:22,978
You awake,

8
00:00:22,978 --> 00:00:26,170
Stretching in bed like a homespun kitten.

9
00:00:26,170 --> 00:00:27,846
Oh aye, there she is,

10
00:00:27,846 --> 00:00:30,399
There is my sweet little miss.

11
00:00:30,399 --> 00:00:33,271
Come come, sun’s all up,

12
00:00:33,271 --> 00:00:38,027
Tide is in, so let’s begin.

13
00:00:38,378 --> 00:00:40,101
“Five more minutes, Tad…”

14
00:00:40,451 --> 00:00:42,447
“Oh aye, but only five more.

15
00:00:42,447 --> 00:00:45,000
Better get going to see what,

16
00:00:45,000 --> 00:00:48,878
What the day has in store”

17
00:00:49,228 --> 00:00:50,984
Sweet so sweet,

18
00:00:50,984 --> 00:00:53,137
My feet knows this street.

19
00:00:53,137 --> 00:00:56,090
Knows the brine and salt,

20
00:00:56,090 --> 00:00:57,606
Set on my skin,

21
00:00:57,606 --> 00:01:00,478
The sea knows,

22
00:01:00,478 --> 00:01:02,713
English-oak hair in the wind.

23
00:01:02,713 --> 00:01:03,988
And I know,

24
00:01:03,988 --> 00:01:07,978
Know this little place is ours.

25
00:01:07,978 --> 00:01:10,212
Pesky picky pastry sweet,

26
00:01:10,212 --> 00:01:21,462
Sweet-sour little heartbeat.

27
00:01:21,462 --> 00:01:22,819
I think, you grow here

28
00:01:22,819 --> 00:01:25,293
Little daffodil dear.

29
00:01:25,293 --> 00:01:27,287
By the seals’ slow call,

30
00:01:27,287 --> 00:01:34,278
A saltflower after all.

31
00:01:34,628 --> 00:01:37,100
Lovely little tiny tousled head,

32
00:01:37,100 --> 00:01:37,978
Breakfast served,

33
00:01:37,978 --> 00:01:39,254
Of course in bed.

34
00:01:39,254 --> 00:01:41,170
Aye, this our getaway

35
00:01:41,170 --> 00:01:44,043
By the cove and Willy’s cave.

36
00:01:44,043 --> 00:01:48,271
Two explorers bold and brave.

37
00:01:48,271 --> 00:01:50,665
Stumble into the morning breeze,

38
00:01:50,665 --> 00:01:53,058
Sun high on the tide and seas.

39
00:01:53,058 --> 00:01:55,531
Let us roam now wild and free.

40
00:01:55,531 --> 00:01:57,605
Past the old Watch House,

41
00:01:57,605 --> 00:01:59,521
By the shore this little mouse.

42
00:01:59,521 --> 00:02:00,956
She runs and skips,

43
00:02:00,956 --> 00:02:02,762
Spray of salt on her lips.

44
00:02:03,111 --> 00:02:04,468
“Tad, tad!

45
00:02:04,468 --> 00:02:06,671
Look, that house is made of shells!”

46
00:02:07,021 --> 00:02:09,495
“Hehe, aye little star.

47
00:02:09,495 --> 00:02:15,209
Shall we go inside?”

48
00:02:15,558 --> 00:02:17,872
Narrow lanes in a ribbon of blue,

49
00:02:17,872 --> 00:02:20,105
Doorframes chipped to a kinder hue,

50
00:02:20,105 --> 00:02:22,500
Fish-baskets dreaming by splintered beams,

51
00:02:22,500 --> 00:02:24,096
Sun stitching gold through the harbour seams.

52
00:02:24,096 --> 00:02:26,808
You point at a cat in a painted frame,

53
00:02:26,808 --> 00:02:29,043
Give every gull a proper name,

54
00:02:29,043 --> 00:02:31,596
Count boat ropes, one to ten,

55
00:02:31,596 --> 00:02:33,989
Lose your place and start again.

56
00:02:33,989 --> 00:02:36,063
Baker’s bell and a saffron bun,

57
00:02:36,063 --> 00:02:38,537
Jam-sticky grin in the Cornish sun,

58
00:02:38,537 --> 00:02:40,611
Cream like clouds on a granite scone,

59
00:02:40,611 --> 00:02:42,925
You hum a tune I’ve always known.

60
00:02:42,925 --> 00:02:45,080
Salt on your lashes, light in your laugh,

61
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:47,872
Sea writes our names in a foamy graph,

62
00:02:47,872 --> 00:02:49,627
And even when the letters go,

63
00:02:49,627 --> 00:02:51,512
The love stays bright below.

64
00:02:51,861 --> 00:02:53,298
Sweet so sweet,

65
00:02:53,298 --> 00:02:56,250
These feet know this street.

66
00:02:56,250 --> 00:02:58,723
Know the brine and the lift,

67
00:02:58,723 --> 00:03:01,116
Of a harbour shift,

68
00:03:01,116 --> 00:03:03,510
Skiff-oars knocking a timbered rhyme,

69
00:03:03,510 --> 00:03:05,903
Ticking the pulse of Polperro time.

70
00:03:05,903 --> 00:03:06,941
And I know,

71
00:03:06,941 --> 00:03:10,850
Know this little place is ours.

72
00:03:10,850 --> 00:03:13,324
Lemon-kissed and pastry-pressed,

73
00:03:13,324 --> 00:03:15,239
Tiny drum of a happy chest.

74
00:03:15,239 --> 00:03:17,394
You bloom where the brine would drown,

75
00:03:17,394 --> 00:03:19,706
Little daffodil in a tidal town,

76
00:03:19,706 --> 00:03:21,543
By the seals’ slow call,

77
00:03:21,543 --> 00:03:25,979
A saltflower after all.

78
00:03:26,330 --> 00:03:28,563
Salt on the brow, salt on the bread,

79
00:03:28,563 --> 00:03:30,956
Salt keeps the tears we thought we shed.

80
00:03:30,956 --> 00:03:33,350
Sea-sweat mingles with the day’s warm light,

81
00:03:33,350 --> 00:03:35,664
Turns every scrape into pearl and white.

82
00:03:35,664 --> 00:03:38,058
What the wave takes, it leaves in kind,

83
00:03:38,058 --> 00:03:42,287
A softer shore, a gentler mind.

84
00:03:42,287 --> 00:03:46,914
Love grows roots in the stony brine,

85
00:03:46,914 --> 00:03:51,512
Breaks through chalk with a quiet spine.

86
00:03:51,861 --> 00:04:16,165
“Tad… listen. The sea is singing.”

87
00:04:16,516 --> 00:04:16,536
[picked mandolin pattern; fiddle answers in lilting phrases,

88
00:04:16,516 --> 00:04:16,536
ripples like sunlight over water, gentle brush of frame rhythm]

89
00:04:16,516 --> 00:04:18,829
Crab lines coiled in a pail of sky,

90
00:04:18,829 --> 00:04:21,302
You squint one eye and you dare them try,

91
00:04:21,302 --> 00:04:23,377
Pebbles pocketed, green, then grey,

92
00:04:23,377 --> 00:04:25,771
We’ll count them home at the end of day.

93
00:04:25,771 --> 00:04:28,004
Cliff-path thyme in a windy prayer,

94
00:04:28,004 --> 00:04:30,399
Gorse sparks yellow in the salted air,

95
00:04:30,399 --> 00:04:32,632
Hand in my hand at the harbour rail,

96
00:04:32,632 --> 00:04:34,786
Watching a gig boat set her sail.

97
00:04:34,786 --> 00:04:36,781
You say, “Tad, when the water goes,

98
00:04:36,781 --> 00:04:39,653
Does it carry our footprints on its toes?”

99
00:04:39,653 --> 00:04:41,649
I say, “Aye, but it keeps, you see,

100
00:04:41,649 --> 00:04:43,802
The little you, safe here with me.”

101
00:04:43,802 --> 00:04:46,435
For here where the world feels small and wide,

102
00:04:46,435 --> 00:04:48,988
You flower straight through the turning tide;

103
00:04:48,988 --> 00:04:51,302
And every tear I couldn’t hide

104
00:04:51,302 --> 00:04:55,500
Turned sweet as kelp in the evening glide.

105
00:04:55,850 --> 00:04:57,048
Sweet so sweet,

106
00:04:57,048 --> 00:04:59,600
My feet knows this street.

107
00:04:59,600 --> 00:05:01,516
Knows the brine and the bite,

108
00:05:01,516 --> 00:05:03,829
And the soft-gold light,

109
00:05:03,829 --> 00:05:06,862
Knows the song in the rigging’s twist,

110
00:05:06,862 --> 00:05:09,495
Copper on the evening mist.

111
00:05:09,495 --> 00:05:11,809
And I know,

112
00:05:11,809 --> 00:05:16,276
Know this little place is ours

113
00:05:16,276 --> 00:05:19,387
Shell-bright laughter, flour-dust hours.

114
00:05:19,387 --> 00:05:24,254
You grew in salt, you grew in sun,

115
00:05:24,254 --> 00:05:29,201
Two hearts knotted and tied as one.

116
00:05:29,201 --> 00:05:33,589
By the seals’ slow call and the harbour wall,

117
00:05:33,589 --> 00:05:40,612
You bloom, you bloom

118
00:05:40,612 --> 00:05:52,548
A saltflower after all.

119
00:05:52,899 --> 00:05:57,605
Sleepy mouse in a tide-rock bed,

120
00:05:57,605 --> 00:06:02,153
Sea hums low while the day turns red.

121
00:06:02,153 --> 00:06:06,463
“Five more minutes?”, aye, take ten.

122
00:06:06,463 --> 00:06:08,776
Tomorrow we’ll roam these lanes again.
